OL,4,CCaptain Underpants: Children's book
OL,5,Cwithdrawn over 'passive racism'
OL,6, A Captain Underpants spin-off book has
OL,7, been taken off sale and children's
OL,8, author Dav Pilkey has apologised for
OL,9, its "harmful racial stereotypes and
OL,10, passively racist imagery".
OL,12,FThe book, titled The Adventures of Ook
OL,13,Fand Gluk: Kung-Fu Cavemen from the
OL,14,FFuture, was first published in 2010.
OL,16,FIn a statement, Pilkey said it was
OL,17,Fmeant to "showcase diversity, equality,
OL,18,Fand non-violent conflict-resolution".
OL,20,FBut he said he now realised it was
OL,21,F"wrong and harmful" to Asian people.
